{
  "id": "infiniflow_ragflow_14767",
  "repo_name": "infiniflow/ragflow",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow",
  "base_commit": "daf8a58c4b26a2e78c5ed5b074ea82ccf40cd4e8",
  "pr_number": 14767,
  "issue_number": 14753,
  "issue_title": "[RFC] Python 3.12 \u2192 3.13 Version Bump",
  "issue_body": "# Python 3.12 \u2192 3.13 Version Bump\n\n## 1. Motivation\n\nPython 3.13 (October 2024) brings significant improvements for RAGFlow's I/O-bound async workload:\n\n- **Free-threading** (PEP 703): No GIL \u2014 notable throughput gains for document processing pipeline\n- **Improved error messages** with color tracebacks\n- **New deprecations** that RAGFlow should stay current with\n\nRAGFlow currently pins `requires-python = \">=3.12,<3.15\"` in `pyproject.toml`. This RFC proposes bumping the floor to 3.13 across all surfaces.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope\n\n### 2.1 Files to Update\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `pyproject.toml:8` | `requires-python = \">=3.12,<3.15\"` \u2192 `\">=3.13,<3.15\"` |\n| `Dockerfile:81` | `uv python install 3.12` \u2192 `3.13` |\n| `Dockerfile:150` | `uv sync --python 3.12 --frozen` \u2192 `3.13` |\n| `.github/workflows/tests.yml:161` | `uv sync --python 3.12 --frozen` \u2192 `3.13` |\n| `.github/workflows/tests.yml:225` | `uv sync --python 3.12 --frozen` \u2192 `3.13` |\n| `CLAUDE.md:121` | `Python 3.10-3.12` \u2192 `Python 3.10-3.13` |\n| `uv.lock` | Regenerated with `uv lock --python 3.13` |\n\n### 2.2 Out of Scope\n\n- Dependency version bumps (only Python version floor changes).\n- Base Docker image changes (not pinned to a specific Python minor version).\n- `docker-compose-base.yml` service images (managed separately).\n\n### 2.3 Lockfile Regeneration (Required, Not Optional)\n\nThe `uv.lock` file **must be regenerated** as part of this change \u2014 there is no post-merge CI job that does this. The frozen lockfile is used directly by `uv sync --frozen` in:\n\n- `Dockerfile:150`\n- `tests.yml:161`\n- `tests.yml:225`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Risk Assessment\n\n### 3.1 Compatibility Risk: **HIGH**\n\nMost packages are safe \u2014 they declare no `<3.13` upper bound. The primary risk is a hard blocker from `graspologic`.\n\n### 3.2 Package Audit Summary\n\n| Package | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| Most dependencies | \u2705 Safe | No `<3.13` upper bound |\n| `graspologic` | \u274c **BLOCKS 3.13** | `requires-python = \">=3.9,<3.13\"` \u2014 hard blocker |\n| `onnxruntime-gpu` | \u26a0\ufe0f Verify | Need to confirm py313 binary wheel exists |\n| `strenum` | \u26a0\ufe0f Monitor | Deprecated, no `requires-python` declared |\n\nFull audit table in [docs/proposals/python-313-upgrade.md](docs/proposals/python-313-upgrade.md).\n\n### 3.3 Critical Blocker: graspologic\n\n**`graspologic`** (`git+https://gitee.com/infiniflow/graspologic.git@38e680cab72...`) is directly imported in first-party graph RAG code:\n\n```\nrag/graphrag/general/entity_embedding.py:13: import graspologic as gc\nrag/graphrag/general/leiden.py:11: from graspologic.partition import hierarchical_leiden\nrag/graphrag/general/leiden.py:12: from graspologic.utils import largest_connected_component\n```\n\nIts `pyproject.toml` declares `requires-python = \">=3.9,<3.13\"` \u2014 it will refuse to install on Python 3.13 under any circumstances.\n\n### 3.4 Resolution Path (Recommended Order)\n\n| Option | Approach | Effort |\n|--------|----------|--------|\n| **A. Fork & patch (recommended first move)** | Fork graspologic, remove `<3.13` cap, retag; update `pyproject.toml:48`; regenerate `uv.lock`; run graph-rag smoke test. | Medium |\n| **B. Local API replacement (fallback if A fails at runtime)** | Replace the narrow API surface in `leiden.py:11-12` and `entity_embedding.py:13` with an alternative or stdlib equivalent. | Medium |\n| **C. Full-package vendoring (last resort)** | Only if A and B both fail due to distribution or governance reasons. | High |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Implementation Notes\n\n### 4.1 PR Structure\n\nSingle PR containing:\n1. All 6 version-pinning file changes (`pyproject.toml`, `Dockerfile`, `tests.yml`, `CLAUDE.md`)\n2. Regenerated `uv.lock` from a clean `uv lock --python 3.13` run\n3. graspologic resolution (fork & patch, per option A above)\n\n### 4.2 Pre-Merge Verification Commands\n\n```bash\n# 1. Check no 3.12 references remain in codebase\ngrep -rn \"3\\.12\" --include=\"*.py\" --include=\"*.yml\" --include=\"*.toml\" --include=\"*.md\" . | grep -v \".git\" | grep -v \"node_modules\"\n\n# 2. Dry-run uv sync with Python 3.13 (CRITICAL \u2014 must pass before merge)\nuv sync --python 3.13 --dry-run\n\n# 3. Verify graspologic constraint\ncurl -s \"https://pypi.org/pypi/graspologic/json\" | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin)\nlatest=max(v for v in d['releases'] if not any(x in v for x in ['a','b','rc','dev']))\nprint('graspologic latest:', latest)\n\"\n\n# 4. Check all == pinned packages for updates needed\nuv pip compile pyproject.toml --python-version 3.13 --dry-run 2>&1 | grep -E \"not found|requires|error|No compatible|\" | head -50\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\nIf a critical incompatibility is discovered post-merge:\n\n1. Revert all file changes (6 version-pinning files + `uv.lock` + graspologic change) to pre-merge state.\n2. Publish a `[breaking]` issue with the error trace.\n3. Revert `requires-python` to `>=3.12,<3.15` in `pyproject.toml` until resolved.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Open Questions\n\n1. **graspologic resolution path**: Fork & patch (Option A) is recommended as first move \u2014 need maintainer approval to fork the `infiniflow/graspologic` repo.\n2. **onnxruntime-gpu wheel availability**: Need to verify binary wheel exists for py313 on target platform (linux/amd64).\n3. **strenum deprecation**: Is strenum used directly in RAGFlow, and if so, what is the migration path to stdlib `enum`?\n\n---\n\n*RFC date: 2026-05-10*\n*Full proposal: [docs/proposals/python-313-upgrade.md](docs/proposals/python-313-upgrade.md)*",
